userStories.description:
Bug

VictoryScene has "Play Again", "Main Menu", and "Exporter" buttons but no button to immediately replay the combat that was just completed. The user must go back to Main Menu → Replays panel to find the saved recording. This is a poor UX flow.
Root Cause

src/scenes/VictoryScene.ts — the create() method only creates Play Again, Main Menu, and Exporter buttons. No Replay button exists.
Fix

Add a "Replay" button to VictoryScene that transitions to ReplayScene with the current recording data:
```typescript
if (this.recording) {
  const replayBtn = this.add.rectangle(centerX, centerY + 290, 200, 50, 0x446688)
    .setInteractive({ useHandCursor: true });
  this.add.text(centerX, centerY + 290, 'Replay', { fontSize: '24px', color: '#ffffff' })
    .setOrigin(0.5);
  replayBtn.on('pointerdown', () => {
    this.scene.start('ReplayScene', this.recording);
  });
}
```
Move the Exporter button down to make room, or reorganize the button layout.
The button should only appear when this.recording exists and has entries (this.recording.entries.length > 0).
Required E2E Tests

- Scenario: VictoryScene shows Replay button when recording has entries — Play a combat to completion. Verify VictoryScene has a "Replay" button visible.
- Scenario: VictoryScene hides Replay button when recording is empty — (Edge case) If recording has 0 entries, the Replay button should not appear.
- Scenario: Clicking Replay transitions to ReplayScene — Click the Replay button. Verify the active scene is ReplayScene and that it received the recording data with non-empty entries.
